To find the allele in the middle of each input, we can split the genotype into three parts and compare each part with the corresponding part in the other two inputs. If the parts are equal for two of the inputs, then the middle allele is the same as the one in the third input.

The following code implements this logic using the inputs given:

```
const inputs = [
  ['uJS 538', 'UJs 73', 'UJS 68', 'uJs 59', 'ujS 71', 'Ujs 530'],
  ['UjS 59', 'ujS 66', 'UJS 68', 'uJs 530', 'UjS 73', 'uJs 59'],
  ['ujs 66', 'UjS 59', 'Ujs 68', 'UjS 530', 'uJs 538', 'ujS 73']
];

for (let i = 0; i < inputs[0].length - 1; i++) {
  const middleAllele = inputs[0][i].match(/uJs+/)[0];
  const firstAllele = inputs[1][i].match(/UJs+/)[0];
  const secondAllele = inputs[0][i+1].match(/UJS+/)[0];

  if (middleAllele === firstAllele && firstAllele === secondAllele && middleAllele!== secondAllele) {
    console.log(middleAllele.toLowerCase().replace('u', ''));
  }
}
```

